<br>
I too, was of the right age to see Star Wars.  I also had a little brother in the same age bracket.  Growing up on Star Wars was amazing and I am glad that our generations children now have their own &quot;Star Wars&quot; aka Phantom Menace.  <br>
<br>
However, I would point out being a GIRL and being into Star Wars was a little different hehe.  You loved it for the romance.  The love triangle between Luke, Han, and Leia.  Yes, I'd run around in flowing white sheets with yarn buns tied to my head thank you very much ~!!!~.  It wasn't about the amazing technology or wonderful effects...that was why my brother liked it. It was about a woman empowered to run a resistance.  She was who I wanted to be.  Along with Wonderwoman, Isis and of course the Bionic Woman.<br>
<br>
As for comparing the two...there is no comparison for me.  One is future one is past.  One is science, one is fanatasy. Both genre's have played a HUGE part in who I have become. One is just as wonderful as the other.<br>
<br>
I sat mesmorized in the theatre in Star Wars and I sat equally mesmorized in Lord of the Rings.  LotR brought me back to being that little girl, waiting for what would happen next.  I was actually holding my breath, squeezing my husband's hand and actually cheering and clapping in some scenes. (I wasn't the only one thank goodness <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )  I have never read the books and will actually read the first one now &lt;not wanting to spoil the rest until I've seen the movies&gt;. But it showed me exactly what I had imagined Elves, dwarfs, goblins, trolls, hobbits, etc to be.  It took me places that before I had only imagined.  It was wonderful seeing it on a huge screen for once.  I think they did a wonderful job.<br>
<br>
I went in a 30-something woman with bills and tons of christmas shopping still weighing on her mind and came out a bright eye'd little girl, swooning over Legolas and Aragorn wanting to be Arwen.  I want the bed sheets, I want the posters, I want it all. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Too bad I don't have kids yet to spoil them rotten with all the &quot;stuff&quot; from this movie.  <br>
<br>
...ponders what a baby's nursery would look like painted as if it was part of an elven city... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
